            <scopecontent id="aspace_d7853cf62d1007565cb5ac4bf79aed5f">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I. contains correspondence from Vachel Lindsay to the poet Sara Teasdale and writings. The letters from Lindsay to Teasdale (later Mrs. Ernst B. Filsinger) document their early courtship and ongoing friendship over nearly two decades. There are also letters from Lindsay's widow, Elizabeth Connor Lindsay, following Lindsay's death in 1931. Most if not all the writings here, chiefly carbons of poems, were originally sent to Teasdale as enclosures to the letters.</p>
            </scopecontent>
